<p>Oh I totally understand the stress on critters, I wouldn't want to add more. Furthermore too clarify two things:<br />
1: I still think its reasonable to say some pages could reach deletion criteria before finding its audience.<br />
2: I do actually agree with the purpose of the high expectations. Even without a successful SCP I've learned valuable things here and appreciate the work.</p>
<p>If you were asking me for suggestions, I think the main thing I'd bring to the table is a more carefree wing of the site. You have the main foundation, the -J's, perhaps a 'Burner Foundation' could be useful? A training ground if you will. A forum where people can post short drafts for fun, and maybe through a system if one becomes popular enough it could be promoted to a full SCP. This is just spitballing but I hope you see what I'm getting at, an alternative, possibly less stressful method to get concepts out. Could have a word maximum, wouldn't need to give critiquers extra work, and allows new people to easily contribute to the site.</p>

